 534:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *  interrupt mask).
 535:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *
 536:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *  An application can use an interrupt callback to know when: 
 537:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *  * the RF activity is about to begin/end; 
 538:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *  * the BLE device changes its state from advertising to connected; 
 539:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *  * BLESS transits between active and low-power modes.
 540:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *    
 541:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *  These BLESS real-time states can be used to synchronize
 542:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *  an application with the BLESS or prevent radio interference with other 
