 680:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** ****************************************************************************//**
 681:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *
 682:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * This function registers an application Host callback (BLE RTOS hook). 
 683:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * The user can trigger an RTOS BLE task if the application Host callback was
 684:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * called.
 685:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * 
 686:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * Theory of operation:
 687:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * The BLE Middleware triggers this callback when the BLE Stack controller needs
 688:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * to process pending Stack events (by calling Cy_BLE_ProcessEvents()). This
 689:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * callback executes from within an ISR and must be very short.  
 690:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *    
 691:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * \note The application Host callback is called from the context of a high-
 692:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * priority ISR. Some RTOS (e.g. FreeRTOS) have restrictions on calling the RTOS
 693:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * functions from a high-priority ISR. The user application is responsible for
 694:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * integration of the BLE RTOS hook and RTOS functions and must insure that RTOS 
 695:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * allows to call RTOS API from BLE interrupt context.  
 696:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * If direct call is forbidden one of the possible solutions is to trig a 
 697:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * low-priority interrupt from the application Host callback and then call the
 698:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * RTOS functions from a low-priority interrupt. For details refer to specific
 699:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * RTOS documentation.
 700:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *   
 701:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * \param CallBack
 702:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * The pointer to the application Host callback.
 703:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *
 704:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** * \return
 705:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *  Error Codes                        | Description
 706:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *  ------------                       | -----------
 707:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *   CY_BLE_SUCCESS                    | The callback was registered successfully.
 708:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *   CY_BLE_ERROR_INVALID_PARAMETER    | On specifying NULL as the input parameter.
 709:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *
 710:Generated_Source\PSoC6\pdl\middleware\ble/cy_ble.c **** *******************************************************************************/
